-- Emirates to order $3 bln in Boeing 777s: sources
-- 
-- Sun Nov 11, 2007 3:18am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/11/11/us-emirates-boeing-idUSL1118967820071111

 

 DUBAI  (Reuters) - Planemaker Boeing Co ( BA.N ) will land an order worth at least $3 billion for its 777 aircraft from Emirates airline EMAIR.UL, sources familiar with the deal said on Sunday. 

 Emirates placed a $31.7 billion order with Boeing rival Airbus ( EAD.PA ) for up to 120 Airbus A350 aircraft and 11 A380 jumbo jets at the Dubai Airshow that started on Sunday. (Reporting by  Jason Neely , Editing by Daliah Merzaban)